ed. Regular and extra sizes 16 to 54. <^Sil\nS nearly two pounds and are ideal\ns for cots and single beds; S\nOPIUM CONFERENCE\nMAY BEHELD HERE\nLeague of Nations Body Pro\nposes World Session on\nDrug Menace.\nBy the Associated Press.\nGENEVA, September 19.\u2014Wash\nington was at today's\nleague of nations discussion of the\nopium problem as the best place to\nhold the proposed* conference In the\nfight\u2019 to be waged against dpium and\nnarcotic drugs. The trend of the de\nbate, however, was that two confer\nences should take place.\nThe first of these conferences\nwould comprise representatives of\ncountries having far eastern posses\nsions and its object would be to sup\npress opium smoking. The states\nconcerned include England. France.\nPortugal, Japan, Holland and India.\nThe second conference would discus\u2019s\nthe limitation of the use of manu\nfactured drugs like morphine and\ncocaine,\nTho league of nations opium cnra\njmission met yesterday, with Stapha'p\n>O. Porter and toe other American\ndelegatee in attendance.\nThe commission received a draft of\nthe report to be made to the league\nassembly. The latter is notable as\nfavoring the passage of a resolution\nwelcoming the co-operation of the\nUnited States government in dealing\nwith the abuse of dangerous drugs.\nIt further requests thp assembly to\nexpress agreement with the proposals\nof the American delegation as em\nbodying.principles which should guide,\nall governments.\nfheso principles are that the A\u00bb\u00abe\nof opium products' should I>e restrict-*\ned to medicinal and scientific pur\nposes and that the production .of\nraw opium. sho'uld be so controlled\nObnoxious Laws I\n\n\u201cI do not like that statute raw\nwhich bans domestic strife; it seems\na most oppressive law, when I would\nbeat my wife.\u201d Thus spake my\nneighbor, Jabez Whence, a voter\nstern and dour, when he'teaned up\nagainst my fence to gossip forian\nhour. \u201cMy wife goes chasing up the\nstreet, she idles and she talks; she\nnever gets me things to eat, she\nnever darns my socks. She never\nheeds the reprimands I hand her\nevery day; she has a mallet in her\nhands, with which she plays croquet.\nShe knows I am a modern hub, by\nmodern rules opprest; she knows' I\nwill not use a club, although a club\nis best. I will not use a club, gad\nzooks, nor tread the caveman\u2019s\nway; the law is there upon the\nbooks,_ I bow and I obey. Although\nthe wife\u2019s a total loss who on my\nbosom leans, I\u2019ll strive to humbly\nbear my cross, and eat cold cans' of\nbeans.\u201d Oh, noble heart, oh, Spar\ntan soul, what sand is in your craw!\nYou yearn to wield a red elm pole,\nand yet obey the law! And cheaper\nskates, and feebler ginks, survey the\nlaw with scorn; they know it\u2019s\nwrong to purchase drinks, and yet\nthey <buy a horn. ...The man heroic\nnever yields to any vain desire that\nleads him to illicit fields, and sets'\nthe law afire.\n(Copyright.) WALT MASON.\n\nthat there frill, be no surplus avail\nable for othep. purposes.\nThe English, delegates to the meet\ning remarked that the American\nrepresentatives .had wisely Insisted\nthat while the manufacture of by\nproducts was being limited, the pro\nduction of thq. raw material also\nshould be limited. J\nA Swlks delegate explained that\nSwitzerland had not adhered to The\nHague;opium convention fpr economic\nreasons. Switzerland, he,said, manu\nfactured druga like cocaine and felt\nIt: was necessary to Investigate the\n,;before taking. \u00a3teps that\nTnighf harm a legitimate, home in\ndustry.\n11\nRADIO MEN TESTIFY\nIN WRECK INQUIRY\nBy the A\u00ab*ocUtetf SIWI.\nSAN DIEGO, Calif., September\nBits of evidence plucked from the air\nnear Point Arguello on the night of\nSeptember 8 last, when seven destroy\ners crashed on the rocks a few miles\nnorth of that promontory, are ex\npected to form the backbone of testi\nmony presented to the naval court of\nInquiry investigating the disaster\nwhen It resumes its sessions here to\nday.\nKadlo men and communications offi\ncers of the destroyer squadron have\n-furnished most of the significant tes\ntimony so far presented to the court.\nFrom the lips of radio men came yes\nterday in the fragmentary form of\nmessages they sent or received dur\ning the hours just preceding the\nwreck, a story of repeated radio sig\nnals Indicating the squadron's posi\ntion some distance north of Point\nArguello, a considerable distance\nabove the point where it would have\nbeen safe to swing eastward into\nSanta Barbara channel.\nTwo minutes after the last of such\nsignals was received, witnesses testi\nfied. Lieut. Donald T. Hunter, captain\nof the squadron flagship Delphy, or\ndered a change of course to the east,\nwhich hurled seven vessels head-on\ninto the rocks of Point Honda,\nJUfet how the fatal order came to\nbe Issued and who was responsible\nfor the apparent misunderstanding of\nthe radio signals remained one of\nthe questions which today\u2019s and other\nsessions of the court were expected\nto answer.\nTestimony of radio men on the\nDelphy that they had been having\ntrouble with their wireless for sev\neral hours before the crash.; that the\nair was crowded with messages, in\nterfering with their attempts to ob\ntain radio compass bearings from\nPoint Arguello indicating the squad\nron portion, and that they sometimes\nwaited as long. ten minutes for\nsuch direction, signal\u00ae indicated some\nof the possible avenues of explana\ntion which further testimony might\ntake.","height":"24921","width":"19551"}}
